creation of repo local and github:-

1)First we create a remote repo on github 
2)we create a local repo and initialize the local by git init and link the local with remote using this command - git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/ai-workflow-backend.git
3)Then we make changes and commit changes stage files and push. 
git add . ----> commit
git commit -m "Initial commit: project setup" ---->commit msg
git push -u origin main ----->push to remote from local


installations and concepts:-

pip install fastapi uvicorn sqlalchemy psycopg2-binary pydantic
1)fastapi the api framework we will use for the project
2)uvicorn is the server use to run locally
3)sqlalchemy- library for working with databases (PostgreSQL in our case).Lets you define models (tables) in Python and interact with the DB using Python code, without writing raw SQL every time.
4)psycopg2-binary -This is the driver that lets Python talk to PostgreSQL.
SQLAlchemy uses this under the hood to actually send commands to PostgreSQL.
5)pydantic---Pydantic helps validate data — ensures user input or API data has the right type (string, int, etc.) before saving it to the DB.
Flow Example (Layman Terms)

User sends POST /users with JSON:
{ "name": "Alice", "email": "alice@example.com" }

Pydantic checks: name is string, email is string, required fields exist
SQLAlchemy converts it into a User row
psycopg2 executes INSERT INTO users ... in PostgreSQL
PostgreSQL stores data → result sent back
SQLAlchemy + Pydantic convert result into JSON → FastAPI returns it
